# MACVM core library load order (sprint_s06_detail.md "Load order").
# Name resolution happens at method-compile time: a file may only
# *reference* globals bound earlier (or in genesis).
01_object.mst
02_nil_boolean.mst
03_behavior.mst
04_transcript.mst
# BlockClosure isn't in the doc's numbered per-class list (a doc gap) but
# must load before any file that sends value/value: for real (05, 06).
04a_blockclosure.mst
05_magnitude.mst
06_smallinteger.mst
07_largeinteger.mst
08_double.mst
# 10 before 09: Character class>>initTable (09's doIt) needs Array>>at:put:
# already installed. See 10_array.mst's header comment.
10_array.mst
09_character.mst
11_bytearray.mst
12_string.mst
13_symbol.mst
14_association.mst
15_ordered.mst
16_dictionary.mst
17_interval.mst
18_writestream.mst
19_printing.mst
20_system.mst
# W1 "library wave 1" additions (WORLD.md's Layer-A/B staged-adoption plan):
# pure extensions of/additions to the classes above, so they load last and
# add nothing earlier files could depend on.
21_collections_ext.mst
22_set.mst
23_fraction.mst
24_readstream.mst
25_sortedcollection.mst
26_bag.mst
27_random.mst
28_point.mst
29_identity_collections.mst
30_date_time.mst
31_readwritestream.mst
32_object_protocol_gaps.mst
# G2 smappl: image-side Visual/Button/Glue widget layer (gui/smappl.md).
33_smappl.mst
# Phase W: reflection mirrors + outliner tools (docs/APPS.md).
34_tools.mst
# Canvas: RGBA pixel buffer (docs/CANVAS.md pixel path) + the Strongtalk 'fast
# floats' Mandelbrot demo that fills one.
36_pixmap.mst
35_mandelbrot.mst
# Canvas demo: libm function plot (sin/cos/exp) via the vector command path.
37_waves.mst
# SIMD vector value classes (docs/SIMD.md) — Float64x2/Float32x4 (+ NEON fuse).
38_simd.mst
# SIMD level 2 (docs/SIMD.md Part E) — FloatArray + explicit-NEON bulk kernels.
39_floatarray.mst
# SequenceableCollection search/copy protocol (Strongtalk port).
40_seqcltn_search.mst
# String splitting utilities (need OrderedCollection; Strongtalk port).
41_string_text.mst
# Benchmark dashboard: live cold/warm perf bar chart on the Canvas.
42_benchdash.mst
# GamePane: drive the native Metal game pane from Smalltalk (M3 slice,
# docs/gamepane_design.md). Numbered game primitives (id block 200+).
43_gamepane.mst
# Breakout: a small but complete demo game exercising the whole engine
# (paddle/ball/brick physics, input, SFX, frame loop; docs/gamepane_design.md).
44_breakout.mst
# MandelZoom: a zooming Mandelbrot rendered live in the game pane (reuses
# Mandelbrot>>escapeAtRe:im:; progressive per-frame render, docs/gamepane_design.md).
45_mandelzoom.mst
# MandelVM: MandelZoom that dives once then stops — the standalone-window demo
# (macvm-gui mandelvm / run-mandelvm.sh) that quits when the demo ends.
46_mandelvm.mst
# Worker: primary/worker VM parallelism, copy-passing messages over MOP pickles
# (docs/multi-smalltalk-worker.md; prims 220-228). Harmless with no worker role.
47_worker.mst
# ParallelMandel: the worker capstone — the MandelZoom dive computed in
# parallel bands by N worker VMs, assembled + blitted by the primary (M4).
48_parallelmandel.mst
